servings: 2
time required: 40 minutes
course: main course
source: https://www.hellofresh.co.uk/recipes/bbq-chicken-5be4271f30006c2526214f82
author: Mimi Morley
---

Preheat your oven to 200°C. Chop the @potatoes{450}(cut into wedges about the size of your index finger, no need to peel). Pop them on a lined #baking tray{} in a single layer. Drizzle over a glug of @oil{glug}, season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Toss to coat. Roast on the top shelf of your oven until browned and slightly crispy, ~{25-30%mins}. Turn halfway through cooking.

Meanwhile, put the @British chicken breasts{2} in a #bowl{} and pour over two-thirds of the @BBQ sauce{64} and a pinch of @salt{} and @pepper{}. Mix together with your hands to ensure the chicken gets a good coating of the sauce. Wrap a rasher of @British streaky bacon{2} around each chicken breast and place on a foil-lined baking tray. Roast the chicken on the middle shelf of your oven for ~{25-30%mins}.

> IMPORTANT: The chicken is cooked when it is no longer pink in the middle.

Drain and rinse the @cannellini beans{1} in a #colander{}. Halve, peel and chop the @onion{1}(peeled and chopped into roughly 1cm pieces). Heat a drizzle of @oil{drizzle} in a #frying pan{} on medium heat, add the onion and cook until soft, ~{5%mins}. Add the @smoked paprika{1/2}, stir and cook for ~{1% minute} more.

Pour in the @tomato passata{1}, the @water{amount}, and the cannellini beans. Season with a pinch of @salt{} and @pepper{} and mix everything together. Simmer gently until reduced, ~{7%mins}. Remove from the heat, add the @baby spinach{125} and pop a lid on. Leave to the side until the spinach has wilted, ~{5-7%mins}, then stir it through your beans. Taste and add more salt and pepper if it needed.

Grate the @mature cheddar cheese{60}. When the chicken is cooked, remove it from your oven and lower the potato wedges to the middle shelf. Preheat your #grill{} to high. Sprinkle the cheese evenly over each chicken breast, then place under your grill until the cheese is brown and bubbling, ~{3-5%mins}.

Serve the BBQ chicken with the potato wedges and homemade baked beans on the side and a dollop of the remaining BBQ sauce. Enjoy!